%N A395692 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of labeled 3-multigraphs on n vertices with clique number exactly k.
%C A395692 A 3-multigraph allows edge multiplicities 0,1,2,3. Clique number is defined on the underlying simple graph (edges with multiplicity >=1).
%C A395692 Part of the family T_p(n,k) = Sum_{G: omega(G)=k} p^{e(G)}. Row sums give 4^(n*(n-1)/2).
%C A395692 The range p=1..5 covers typical transportation network interlining depths (metro/tram systems). See cross-references for other p values.
%C A395692 Values computed by weighting simple graph enumeration with 3^{e(G)}; verified for n<=6.
%H A395692 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A395692/b395692.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..66</a>
%H A395692 Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20004703">Clique-Size Dominance Threshold Distribution Enumerating Labeled Graphs by Clique Number and the Minimum Coding Clique Size</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%H A395692 Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales, <a href="https://github.com/alejandrozu/Clique-OEIS">Python verification code and Lean 4 formalization</a>, GitHub.
%F A395692 T(n,k) = Sum_{G: omega(G)=k} 3^{e(G)}.
%F A395692 Row sum: Sum_{k=1..n} T(n,k) = 4^(n*(n-1)/2).
